body_html:
Any suggestion on how I could trace tensorflow core calls in C++ land so we can identify the problem?

I tried dtrace and tfdbg, however dtrace got me only syscalls and tfdbg only python / graph related things.

Okay so tf.parse_single_example or tf.parse_example etc. pp. (see comment below), all finally end up at ExampleParserOp which uses FastParseSerializedExample and ParseExample where our error occur.

body:
~~Any suggestion on how I could trace tensorflow core calls in C++ land so we can identify the problem?~~

~~I tried dtrace and tfdbg, however dtrace got me only syscalls and tfdbg only python / graph related things.~~

Okay so `tf.parse_single_example` or `tf.parse_example` etc. pp. (see comment below), all finally end up at [`ExampleParserOp`][1] which uses [`FastParseSerializedExample`][2] and [`ParseExample`][3]  where our error occur.

[1]: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/b126091bbb65e614d43d6ccd984e728561778a1a/tensorflow/core/kernels/example_parsing_ops.cc#L142
[2]: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/e062447136faa0a3513e3b0690598fee5c16a5db/tensorflow/core/util/example_proto_fast_parsing.cc#L461-L462
[3]: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/e062447136faa0a3513e3b0690598fee5c16a5db/tensorflow/core/util/example_proto_fast_parsing.cc#L298-L321
